Replace or correct values in the columns. 4


Just like in step 3.6, this time replace misspelled values, blank values or other invalid characters like dashes or commas. Blank values, commas, dashes, or unclear values will be replaced by Unknown.








Step 4.1 Apply trim from transformation to clean extra spaces.

1. Right click on the column header.

2. Go to transform and select Trim.



 



Step 4.2 Correct misspelled values.

1. Select the column.

2. Go to the Transform tab.

3. Select Replace Values

4. Type in the value to be replaced in the Value To Find field. In this case black

5. Type in the correct value on the Replace With filed. In this case Black.

6. Open the Advance option tab and select Match entire cell contents.

7. Click Ok.





Repeat the previous steps to replace the remaining misspelled values. Remember to replace unclear and - with the value Unknown

You should end with the following values:



https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/replace-values-power-query-28256517-f1e9-4dc3-832f-45786e9cf721
